        {/* Community Sentiment - Digital Ethnography of Expatriate Healthcare Discourse */}
        <TabsContent value="sentiment" className="space-y-6">
          {/* Executive Summary */}
          <GlassPanel
            title="Digital Ethnography: Expatriate Healthcare Discourse"
            description="Structural and sentiment analysis of Reddit, ExpatWoman, and niche forums"
            badge="50 Threads"
          >
            <div className="rounded-lg bg-purple-50 border border-purple-200 p-4">
              <p className="text-sm text-purple-800 font-semibold mb-2">DIGITAL ANTHROPOLOGY STUDY</p>
              <p className="text-xs text-slate-700 mb-3">
                Digital forums have replaced the town square as primary locus of community knowledge transfer. For expatriates, these are survival mechanisms—shadow legal clinics where users crowdsource strategies to mitigate state-imposed fines and navigate healthcare.
              </p>
              <div className="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3">
                <div className="rounded bg-white p-2 border border-purple-200">
                  <p className="text-sm font-bold text-purple-600">"Peer-to-Peer Regulation"</p>
                  <p className="text-xs text-slate-600">Community members guide each other through opaque bureaucracies</p>
                </div>
                <div className="rounded bg-white p-2 border border-purple-200">
                  <p className="text-sm font-bold text-amber-600">"Trust is Personal"</p>
                  <p className="text-xs text-slate-600">Hospital brand is less than Doctor&apos;s name; loopholes greater than compliance</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </GlassPanel>

          {/* The Legal-Medical Nexus */}
          <GlassPanel title="The Legal-Medical Nexus" description="Insurance, fines, and residency anxiety" badge="Critical">
            <div className="space-y-4">
              <div className="grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-2">
                <div className="rounded-lg bg-rose-50 p-4 border border-rose-200">
                  <h4 className="font-bold text-rose-900 mb-2">The "Innocent Transgressor"</h4>
                  <p className="text-xs text-rose-800 mb-2">
                    Expatriates who intend to comply but are thwarted by employer negligence or systemic friction.
                  </p>
                  <div className="rounded bg-white p-2 border border-rose-200">
                    <p className="text-xs text-slate-700 italic">"My previous employer did not renew my health insurance, and he was unresponsive, closed their phone, leaving me without coverage"</p>
                  </div>
                  <div className="mt-2 rounded bg-amber-100 p-2 border border-amber-300">
                    <p className="text-xs text-amber-800">Consensus: Moral innocence ≠ Legal immunity. Fines inevitable unless broker (Bayzat) intervenes.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div className="rounded-lg bg-amber-50 p-4 border border-amber-200">
                  <h4 className="font-bold text-amber-900 mb-2">Golden Visa "Scam" Narrative</h4>
                  <p className="text-xs text-amber-800 mb-2">
                    Long-term residents abroad still subject to insurance mandates.
                  </p>
                  <div className="rounded bg-white p-2 border border-amber-200">
                    <p className="text-xs text-slate-700 italic">"A massive scam to help trick people into staying... monthly fines while not resident"</p>
                  </div>
                  <div className="mt-2 rounded bg-purple-100 p-2 border border-purple-300">
                    <p className="text-xs text-purple-800">Compliance Fatigue: Buy cheapest "junk" insurance as "residency tax"</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div className="rounded-lg bg-cyan-50 p-4 border border-cyan-200">
                <h4 className="font-bold text-cyan-900 mb-2">Strategic Non-Compliance: The "Provider Switch" Maneuver</h4>
                <p className="text-xs text-cyan-800 mb-2">
                  Community sophistication in "gaming" system to avoid penalties.
                </p>
                <div className="rounded bg-white p-2 border border-cyan-200">
                  <p className="text-xs text-slate-700 italic">"Apply for another insurance company for a year and then move back to the old provider. New provider (AXA/AIG) won't look at gap left by Daman."</p>
                </div>
                <div className="mt-2 rounded bg-emerald-100 p-2 border border-emerald-300">
                  <p className="text-xs text-emerald-800">Consensus: Loyalty to single insurer dangerous; fluidity required to avoid automated fines.</p>
                </div>
              </div>

              {/* Insurance Discussion Threads Table */}
              <div className="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 p-4 border border-slate-200">
                <h4 className="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Community Analysis of Insurance Discussion Threads</h4>
                <div className="space-y-2 text-xs">
                  {[
                    { id: '1', topic: 'Employer Negligence & Fines', anxiety: 'Paying for employer\'s error', sentiment: 'High Anxiety. Fines inevitable unless broker intervenes.', color: 'rose' },
                    { id: '2', topic: 'Golden Visa & Abroad Status', anxiety: 'Monthly fines while not resident', sentiment: 'Compliance Fatigue. Buy cheapest junk insurance.', color: 'amber' },
                    { id: '3', topic: 'Golden Visa Validity', anxiety: 'Is the visa a "scam"?', sentiment: 'Skepticism. Hidden costs make it less attractive.', color: 'purple' },
                    { id: '4', topic: 'Gap in Coverage (Job Switch)', anxiety: 'Fines during visa transition', sentiment: 'Strategic Avoidance. Switch providers to reset fine clock.', color: 'cyan' },
                    { id: '25', topic: 'General Insurance Types', anxiety: 'Fear of catastrophe', sentiment: 'Risk Aversion. Shield against bankruptcy (100k+ bills).', color: 'emerald' },
                  ].map((item) => (
                    <div key={item.id} className={`rounded p-2 border-l-2 ${
                      item.color === 'rose' ? 'bg-rose-50 border-rose-400' :
                      item.color === 'amber' ? 'bg-amber-50 border-amber-400' :
                      item.color === 'purple' ? 'bg-purple-50 border-purple-400' :
                      item.color === 'cyan' ? 'bg-cyan-50 border-cyan-400' :
                      'bg-emerald-50 border-emerald-400'
                    }`}>
                      <div className="flex items-start justify-between gap-2">
                        <div>
                          <p className="font-semibold text-slate-900">{item.topic}</p>
                          <p className="text-slate-600">{item.anxiety}</p>
                        </div>
                        <Badge variant={item.color === 'rose' ? 'destructive' : item.color === 'amber' ? 'warning' : item.color === 'purple' ? 'purple' : item.color === 'cyan' ? 'cyan' : 'emerald'} className="text-xs shrink-0">
                          #{item.id}
                        </Badge>
                      </div>
                      <p className="mt-1 text-slate-700">{item.sentiment}</p>
                    </div>
                  ))}
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </GlassPanel>

          {/* The Maternity Marketplace */}
          <GlassPanel title="The Maternity Marketplace" description="Commodification, anxiety, and hospital choice" badge="Cost Analysis">
            <div className="space-y-4">
              <div className="grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-2">
                {/* Corniche - Safety Fortress */}
                <Card className="glass-card border-t-4 border-t-teal-500">
                  <CardHeader className="pb-3">
                    <div className="flex items-center justify-between">
                      <CardTitle className="text-base">Corniche Hospital</CardTitle>
                      <Badge variant="teal">Safety First</Badge>
