                  A profound anthropological insight - expatriate mothers' visceral fear of babies being "mixed or exchanged in newborn units."
                </p>
                <div className="rounded bg-white p-2 border border-rose-200">
                  <p className="text-xs text-slate-700 italic">"Do they have a system to prevent babies mixing? I'm worried about my baby at Al Noor Hospital."</p>
                </div>
                <div className="mt-2 rounded bg-amber-100 p-2 border border-amber-300">
                  <p className="text-xs text-amber-800">Analysis: Fear not about administrative error - manifestation of cultural alienation projecting onto biological continuity.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
