        <TabsContent value="blogscout" className="space-y-6">
          <GlassPanel title="Niche Content Monitor" description="Independent voices and influencer landscape in Abu Dhabi healthcare discourse">
            <div className="space-y-6">
              {/* Executive Summary */}
              <Card className="glass-card">
                <CardHeader>
                  <CardTitle className="text-lg flex items-center gap-2">
                    <Radar className="h-5 w-5 text-purple-500" />
                    Digital Topography of Healthcare
                  </CardTitle>
                  <CardDescription>The Trust Void and Narrative Landscape</CardDescription>
                </CardHeader>
                <CardContent>
                  <div className="space-y-4">
                    <div className="rounded-lg bg-purple-50 border border-purple-200 p-4">
                      <div className="flex items-start gap-3">
                        <AlertCircle className="h-5 w-5 text-purple-500 mt-0.5" />
                        <div>
                          <h5 className="font-semibold text-purple-900">The Trust Void</h5>
                          <p className="text-sm text-purple-700 mt-1">
                            A striking feature of the independent content ecosystem is the absence of centralized &quot;go-to&quot; resources for navigating the Abu Dhabi healthcare system. Expatriates, in particular, rely heavily on peer-to-peer knowledge sharing within Facebook groups, WhatsApp broadcasts, and Reddit threads rather than official channels.
                          </p>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div className="grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-2">
                      <div className="rounded-lg bg-white border border-slate-200 p-4">
                        <h6 className="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">Narrative of Vulnerability vs. Compliance</h6>
                        <p className="text-xs text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                          The dominant sentiment in independent healthcare discourse is one of vulnerability—particularly among expats navigating mandatory insurance, fines, and tiered access. This contrasts sharply with official narratives of compliance and world-class care. The gap between policy rhetoric and lived experience creates fertile ground for misinformation and anxiety.
                        </p>
                      </div>
                      <div className="rounded-lg bg-white border border-slate-200 p-4">
                        <h6 className="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">The Information Paradox</h6>
                        <p className="text-xs text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                          Despite 3.5B+ records in Malaffi and sophisticated digital infrastructure, patients still resort to informal networks for basic information like &quot;which hospital accepts my insurance&quot; or &quot;is this doctor any good.&quot; This suggests a failure of user experience design in official healthcare apps.
                        </p>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </CardContent>
              </Card>

              {/* Maternity Narrative */}
              <Card className="glass-card">
                <CardHeader>
                  <CardTitle className="text-lg flex items-center gap-2">
                    <Heart className="h-5 w-5 text-rose-500" />
                    The Maternity Narrative: Birth Warriors and Digital Tribes
                  </CardTitle>
                  <CardDescription>The most vocal and organized healthcare community</CardDescription>
                </CardHeader>
                <CardContent>
                  <div className="space-y-4">
                    <div className="rounded-lg bg-rose-50 border border-rose-200 p-4">
                      <h5 className="font-semibold text-rose-900 mb-2">The &quot;Birth Warrior&quot; Archetype</h5>
                      <p className="text-sm text-rose-700 leading-relaxed">
                        Maternity content creators in Abu Dhabi have adopted the language of combat—&quot;birth warrior,&quot; &quot;advocacy,&quot; &quot;informed consent,&quot; &quot;defying protocol.&quot; This reflects a desire for agency in a medical system that can feel paternalistic. Doulas and birth coaches have emerged as critical bridge nodes between the medical establishment and expectant mothers.
                      </p>
                    </div>

                    <div className="rounded-lg bg-white border border-slate-200 p-4">
                      <h6 className="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">The Doula Movement</h6>
                      <p className="text-sm text-slate-600 mb-3">
                        A significant development is the professionalization of birth support. Doulas like &quot;The Empowered Doula&quot; and birth coaches offer services ranging from birth plan creation to hospital advocacy. They position themselves as the patient&apos;s voice in the delivery room, particularly in C-section scenarios where mothers feel pressured.
                      </p>
                      <div className="grid gap-2 text-xs">
                        <div className="flex items-start gap-2">
                          <CheckCircle2 className="h-4 w-4 text-emerald-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" />
                          <span className="text-slate-600"><strong>Water Birth Demand:</strong> Specific demand for water birth facilities has created hospital brand perception differentiation.</span>
                        </div>
                        <div className="flex items-start gap-2">
                          <CheckCircle2 className="h-4 w-4 text-emerald-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" />
                          <span className="text-slate-600"><strong>Hospital Brand Loyalty:</strong> Maternity experiences create lifelong hospital loyalty—positive birth stories = family brand champions.</span>
                        </div>
                        <div className="flex items-start gap-2">
                          <CheckCircle2 className="h-4 w-4 text-emerald-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" />
                          <span className="text-slate-600"><strong>Digital Communities:</strong> Private Facebook groups (e.g., &quot;Abu Dhabi Births&quot;) serve as safe spaces for sharing doctor recommendations and warning about &quot;bossy&quot; consultants.</span>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>

                    {/* Hospital Brand Perception Map */}
                    <div className="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
                      <h6 className="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">Hospital Brand Perception Map (Maternity Focus)</h6>
                      <ScrollArea className="h-[300px]">
                        <table className="w-full text-xs">
                          <thead className="sticky top-0 bg-slate-50 border-b border-slate-200">
                            <tr>
                              <th className="text-left p-2 font-semibold text-slate-900">Hospital</th>
                              <th className="text-left p-2 font-semibold text-slate-900">Perception</th>
                              <th className="text-left p-2 font-semibold text-slate-900">Key Attributes</th>
                              <th className="text-left p-2 font-semibold text-slate-900">Sentiment</th>
                            </tr>
                          </thead>
                          <tbody>
                            {hospitalBrandPerception.map((hospital, idx) => (
                              <tr key={idx} className="border-b border-slate-100 hover:bg-white">
                                <td className="p-2 font-medium text-slate-900">{hospital.name}</td>
                                <td className="p-2 text-slate-600">{hospital.perception}</td>
                                <td className="p-2 text-slate-600">{hospital.attributes}</td>
                                <td className="p-2">
                                  <Badge variant={hospital.sentimentBadge} className="text-xs">{hospital.sentiment}</Badge>
                                </td>
                              </tr>
                            ))}
                          </tbody>
                        </table>
                      </ScrollArea>
                    </div>

                    {/* Water Birth Peak Experiences */}
                    <div className="rounded-lg bg-cyan-50 border border-cyan-200 p-4">
                      <h6 className="font-semibold text-cyan-900 mb-2">Water Birth: The Premium Experience</h6>
                      <p className="text-sm text-cyan-700 mb-2">
                        Water birth has emerged as a status symbol and &quot;peak experience&quot; in Abu Dhabi maternity care. Only a subset of hospitals offer true water birth facilities (not just labor tubs), and this creates differentiation.
                      </p>
                      <div className="grid gap-2 lg:grid-cols-2">
                        <div className="rounded-lg bg-white p-3 border border-cyan-100">
                          <div className="text-xs font-semibold text-slate-900">The &quot;Hotel&quot; Factor</div>
                          <p className="text-xs text-slate-600 mt-1">Reviews consistently compare maternity wards to hotels—food quality, room service, and postpartum care are discussed as much as medical outcomes.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div className="rounded-lg bg-white p-3 border border-cyan-100">
                          <div className="text-xs font-semibold text-slate-900">Price Transparency Gap</div>
                          <p className="text-xs text-slate-600 mt-1">Exact maternity package costs are difficult to ascertain upfront, leading to surprise billing complaints—a major friction point.</p>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </CardContent>
              </Card>

              {/* Elective & Aesthetic Health */}
              <Card className="glass-card">
                <CardHeader>
                  <CardTitle className="text-lg flex items-center gap-2">
                    <Sparkles className="h-5 w-5 text-purple-500" />
                    Elective &amp; Aesthetic Health: The Journey Genre
                  </CardTitle>
                  <CardDescription>From LASIK to Hollywood Smile—personal transformation narratives</CardDescription>
                </CardHeader>
                <CardContent>
                  <div className="space-y-4">
                    <p className="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                      A significant category of independent healthcare content focuses on elective procedures—LASIK eye surgery, dental work (&quot;Hollywood Smile&quot;), laser hair removal, and skincare. These are framed as &quot;journeys&quot; rather than medical procedures, with creators documenting before/after results, recovery timelines, and cost breakdowns.
                    </p>

                    <div className="grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-3">
                      <div className="rounded-lg bg-purple-50 border border-purple-200 p-4">
                        <div className="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                          <Eye className="h-4 w-4 text-purple-500" />
                          <h6 className="font-semibold text-purple-900">LASIK Journeys</h6>
                        </div>
                        <p className="text-xs text-purple-700">
                          Detailed accounts of LASIK surgery at various Abu Dhabi clinics (Moorfields, Magrabi). Creators share surgery videos, immediate post-op pain levels, and &quot;life without glasses&quot; revelations. Clinic selection heavily influenced by doctor reputation over brand.
                        </p>
                      </div>

                      <div className="rounded-lg bg-rose-50 border border-rose-200 p-4">
                        <div className="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                          <Star className="h-4 w-4 text-rose-500" />
                          <h6 className="font-semibold text-rose-900">Hollywood Smile</h6>
                        </div>
                        <p className="text-xs text-rose-700">
                          Dental veneer packages are heavily marketed and reviewed. &quot;Turkish teeth&quot; comparisons appear frequently. Cost comparisons between Dubai vs. Abu Dhabi clinics drive decision-making. Dubai perceived as more premium/pricier.
                        </p>
                      </div>

                      <div className="rounded-lg bg-cyan-50 border border-cyan-200 p-4">
                        <div className="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                          <Zap className="h-4 w-4 text-cyan-500" />
                          <h6 className="font-semibold text-cyan-900">Laser Hair Removal</h6>
                        </div>
                        <p className="text-xs text-cyan-700">
                          Long-term reviews (6-12 months) of laser hair removal results. Brazilian/Bikini areas discussed candidly. &quot;Glass Skin&quot; and Korean skincare routines influence treatment choices. Full-body laser packages as status investment.
                        </p>
                      </div>
                    </div>

                    <div className="rounded-lg bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 p-4">
                      <h6 className="font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Key Insight: The &quot;Turkish Dentist&quot; Competition</h6>
                      <p className="text-sm text-amber-700">
                        Abu Dhabi dental clinics face implicit competition from Turkish dental tourism. Many creators explicitly compare local quotes to Turkish package deals. Local clinics counter with &quot;convenience,&quot; &quot;follow-up care,&quot; and &quot;same-day service&quot; narratives.
                      </p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </CardContent>
              </Card>

              {/* Expat Survival Guide */}
              <Card className="glass-card">
                <CardHeader>
                  <CardTitle className="text-lg flex items-center gap-2">
                    <AlertTriangle className="h-5 w-5 text-amber-500" />
                    The Expat Survival Guide: Insurance, Fines, and Tiered Reality
                  </CardTitle>
                  <CardDescription>Practical healthcare navigation content for expatriates</CardDescription>
                </CardHeader>
                <CardContent>
                  <div className="space-y-4">
                    <div className="rounded-lg bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 p-4">
                      <h5 className="font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Mandatory Insurance: The Fine Fear</h5>
                      <p className="text-sm text-amber-700 leading-relaxed">
                        A dominant content category involves explaining—and often warning about—Abu Dhabi&apos;s mandatory health insurance system. Content creators break down the difference between Thiqa (for nationals) and Daman/AXA/GIG (for expats), with particular focus on fines for non-compliance.
                      </p>
                    </div>

                    <div className="grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-2">
                      <div className="rounded-lg bg-white border border-slate-200 p-4">
                        <h6 className="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">The AED 500/Month Fear</h6>
                        <p className="text-xs text-slate-600 mb-2">
                          Viral threads warn about the AED 500/month fine for not providing health insurance to domestic workers. This specific penalty has become legendary in expat circles and drives insurance uptake.
                        </p>
                        <div className="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs">
                          <Badge variant="warning">High Anxiety</Badge>
                          <span className="text-slate-500">Frequently shared in domestic worker groups</span>
                        </div>
                      </div>

                      <div className="rounded-lg bg-white border border-slate-200 p-4">
                        <h6 className="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">The Golden Visa Dilemma</h6>
                        <p className="text-xs text-slate-600 mb-2">
                          Healthcare access is a key consideration for Golden Visa applicants. Content explores which insurance packages meet visa requirements and whether private insurance is necessary for high-net-worth individuals.
                        </p>
                        <div className="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs">
                          <Badge variant="info">Niche Audience</Badge>
                          <span className="text-slate-500">HNW expat decision-makers</span>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>

                    <div className="rounded-lg bg-rose-50 border border-rose-200 p-4">
                      <h6 className="font-semibold text-rose-900 mb-2">Tiered Healthcare Reality</h6>
                      <p className="text-sm text-rose-700">
                        Expat content creators frequently discuss the &quot;tiered&quot; nature of Abu Dhabi healthcare—basic insurance (essential benefits plan) vs. enhanced plans. There is palpable resentment about &quot;VIP&quot; fast-track services for those who can pay, while basic plan holders wait for appointments.
                      </p>
                      <div className="mt-3 grid gap-2 text-xs">
                        <div className="flex items-start gap-2">
                          <AlertCircle className="h-4 w-4 text-rose-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" />
                          <span className="text-rose-700"><strong>&quot;Second Class&quot; Sentiment:</strong> Some expats describe feeling like &quot;second class&quot; citizens in the healthcare system compared to Emiratis with Thiqa.</span>
                        </div>
                        <div className="flex items-start gap-2">
                          <AlertCircle className="h-4 w-4 text-rose-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" />
                          <span className="text-rose-700"><strong>Claim Rejection Trauma:</strong> Stories about denied insurance claims (especially for pre-existing conditions) go viral and damage trust in the system.</span>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </CardContent>
              </Card>

              {/* Professional & Technical Voice */}
              <Card className="glass-card">
                <CardHeader>
                  <CardTitle className="text-lg flex items-center gap-2">
                    <Building2 className="h-5 w-5 text-denim-500" />
                    The Professional &amp; Tech Voice: Smart Health and Career Perspectives
                  </CardTitle>
                  <CardDescription>Doctors, startups, and industry professionals</CardDescription>
                </CardHeader>
                <CardContent>
                  <div className="space-y-4">
                    <div className="rounded-lg bg-denim-50 border border-denim-200 p-4">
                      <h5 className="font-semibold text-denim-900 mb-2">Smart Health Dubai / Abu Dhabi</h5>
                      <p className="text-sm text-denim-700 leading-relaxed">
                        While not a single influencer, the &quot;Smart Health&quot; conference and ecosystem has generated significant professional content. Doctors share keynotes, panel discussions, and networking insights from these events. The narrative positions UAE as a &quot;Silicon Valley for HealthTech.&quot;
                      </p>
                    </div>

                    <div className="grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-2">
                      <div className="rounded-lg bg-white border border-slate-200 p-4">
                        <h6 className="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">Medical Tourism Reversal</h6>
                        <p className="text-xs text-slate-600">
                          Professional content increasingly highlights the &quot;reverse flow&quot; of patients—from West to East. Case studies of patients traveling from USA/UK to Abu Dhabi for complex procedures (robotic surgery, transplants) are shared as validation of the system&apos;s maturity.
                        </p>
                      </div>

                      <div className="rounded-lg bg-white border border-slate-200 p-4">
                        <h6 className="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">Doctor Career Content</h6>
                        <p className="text-xs text-slate-600">
                          LinkedIn-style content from doctors discussing career pathways, Emiratisation, salary benchmarks, and the distinction between private vs. government (SEHA/DoH) employment. This serves as recruitment and retention communication.
                        </p>
                      </div>
                    </div>

                    <div className="rounded-lg bg-emerald-50 border border-emerald-200 p-4">
                      <h6 className="font-semibold text-emerald-900 mb-2">Startup Ecosystem Voices</h6>
                      <p className="text-sm text-emerald-700">
                        HealthTech startup founders (e.g., from Hub71, twofour54) share founder journeys, funding announcements, and product launches. This content targets investors, partners, and early adopters rather than patients. Examples include digital therapeutics, telemedicine platforms, and AI diagnostics.
                      </p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </CardContent>
              </Card>

              {/* The 50 Voices Compendium */}
              <Card className="glass-card border-l-4 border-l-purple-500">
                <CardHeader>
                  <CardTitle className="text-lg flex items-center gap-2">
                    <Users className="h-5 w-5 text-purple-500" />
                    The 50 Voices Compendium
                  </CardTitle>
                  <CardDescription>Independent and semi-independent voices shaping Abu Dhabi healthcare discourse</CardDescription>
                </CardHeader>
                <CardContent>
                  <div className="space-y-6">
                    {/* Category 1: Maternity & Birth Stories */}
                    <div>
                      <h6 className="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
                        <Badge variant="rose" className="text-xs">Category 1</Badge>
                        Maternity &amp; Birth Stories (20 voices)
                      </h6>
                      <ScrollArea className="h-[300px]">
                        <table className="w-full text-xs">
