                                  <div className="font-medium text-slate-900">{voice.title}</div>
                                  {voice.url && <div className="text-xs text-amber-600 truncate">{voice.url}</div>}
                                </td>
                                <td className="p-2 text-slate-600">{voice.takeaway}</td>
                              </tr>
                            ))}
                          </tbody>
                        </table>
                      </ScrollArea>
                    </div>

                    {/* Category 3: Elective Health, Aesthetics & Innovation */}
                    <div>
                      <h6 className="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
                        <Badge variant="purple" className="text-xs">Category 3</Badge>
                        Elective Health, Aesthetics &amp; Innovation (10 voices)
                      </h6>
                      <ScrollArea className="h-[200px]">
                        <table className="w-full text-xs">
                          <thead className="sticky top-0 bg-slate-50 border-b border-slate-200">
                            <tr>
                              <th className="text-left p-2 font-semibold text-slate-900 w-12">#</th>
                              <th className="text-left p-2 font-semibold text-slate-900">Source Title</th>
                              <th className="text-left p-2 font-semibold text-slate-900">Key Takeaway</th>
                            </tr>
                          </thead>
                          <tbody>
                            {aestheticVoices.map((voice, idx) => (
                              <tr key={idx} className="border-b border-slate-100 hover:bg-white">
                                <td className="p-2 text-slate-500">{idx + 1}</td>
                                <td className="p-2">
                                  <div className="font-medium text-slate-900">{voice.title}</div>
                                  {voice.url && <div className="text-xs text-purple-600 truncate">{voice.url}</div>}
                                </td>
                                <td className="p-2 text-slate-600">{voice.takeaway}</td>
                              </tr>
                            ))}
                          </tbody>
                        </table>
                      </ScrollArea>
                    </div>

                    {/* Category 4: Professional Voices, Tech & Reviews */}
                    <div>
                      <h6 className="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
                        <Badge variant="denim" className="text-xs">Category 4</Badge>
                        Professional Voices, Tech &amp; Reviews (10 voices)
                      </h6>
                      <ScrollArea className="h-[200px]">
                        <table className="w-full text-xs">
                          <thead className="sticky top-0 bg-slate-50 border-b border-slate-200">
                            <tr>
                              <th className="text-left p-2 font-semibold text-slate-900 w-12">#</th>
                              <th className="text-left p-2 font-semibold text-slate-900">Source Title</th>
                              <th className="text-left p-2 font-semibold text-slate-900">Key Takeaway</th>
                            </tr>
                          </thead>
                          <tbody>
                            {professionalVoices.map((voice, idx) => (
                              <tr key={idx} className="border-b border-slate-100 hover:bg-white">
                                <td className="p-2 text-slate-500">{idx + 1}</td>
                                <td className="p-2">
                                  <div className="font-medium text-slate-900">{voice.title}</div>
                                  {voice.url && <div className="text-xs text-denim-600 truncate">{voice.url}</div>}
                                </td>
                                <td className="p-2 text-slate-600">{voice.takeaway}</td>
                              </tr>
                            ))}
                          </tbody>
                        </table>
                      </ScrollArea>
                    </div>

                    {/* Strategic Conclusions */}
                    <div className="rounded-lg bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-50 to-rose-50 border border-purple-200 p-4">
                      <h6 className="font-semibold text-purple-900 mb-3">Strategic Conclusions: The Independent Voice Landscape</h6>
                      <div className="grid gap-3 lg:grid-cols-2">
                        <div className="flex items-start gap-2">
                          <CheckCircle2 className="h-4 w-4 text-emerald-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" />
                          <p className="text-xs text-slate-700"><strong>Maternity is the loudest vertical:</strong> No other healthcare topic generates as much independent content, passion, or brand loyalty as childbirth.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div className="flex items-start gap-2">
                          <CheckCircle2 className="h-4 w-4 text-emerald-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" />
                          <p className="text-xs text-slate-700"><strong>Insurance friction is the silent crisis:</strong> Confusion about plans, fines, and claims is a persistent theme that undermines trust.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div className="flex items-start gap-2">
                          <CheckCircle2 className="h-4 w-4 text-emerald-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" />
                          <p className="text-xs text-slate-700"><strong>Doula influence is underrated:</strong> Birth coaches wield disproportionate influence over hospital choice and birth plans.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div className="flex items-start gap-2">
                          <CheckCircle2 className="h-4 w-4 text-emerald-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" />
                          <p className="text-xs text-slate-700"><strong>Aesthetic procedures drive clinic selection:</strong> LASIK and dental reviews serve as proxies for overall clinic quality.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div className="flex items-start gap-2">
                          <CheckCircle2 className="h-4 w-4 text-emerald-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" />
                          <p className="text-xs text-slate-700"><strong>Expat vulnerability creates opportunity:</strong> The &quot;survival guide&quot; content gap represents an opportunity for official clarifications.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div className="flex items-start gap-2">
                          <CheckCircle2 className="h-4 w-4 text-emerald-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" />
                          <p className="text-xs text-slate-700"><strong>Professional content is B2B-focused:</strong> Doctor and startup content targets industry, not patients, indicating a disconnect in patient education.</p>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </CardContent>
              </Card>
            </div>
          </GlassPanel>
        </TabsContent>

        {/* File 19: Crisis News Audit - Global Crisis Radar */}
        <TabsContent value="crisisaudit" className="space-y-6">
          <GlassPanel title="Global Crisis Radar" description="Healthcare vulnerability audit and threat detection matrix (2023-2025)">
            <div className="space-y-6">
              {/* Executive Summary */}
              <Card className="glass-card border-l-4 border-l-rose-500">
                <CardHeader>
                  <CardTitle className="text-lg flex items-center gap-2">
                    <AlertTriangle className="h-5 w-5 text-rose-500" />
                    The Architecture of Systemic Collapse
                  </CardTitle>
                  <CardDescription>Global Healthcare Vulnerability Audit: 50 Critical Threat Indicators</CardDescription>
                </CardHeader>
                <CardContent>
                  <div className="space-y-4">
                    <div className="rounded-lg bg-rose-50 border border-rose-200 p-4">
                      <h5 className="font-semibold text-rose-900 mb-2">Critical Finding: Poly-Crisis Convergence</h5>
                      <p className="text-sm text-rose-700 leading-relaxed">
                        The global healthcare ecosystem is undergoing accelerated disintegration. We are witnessing the transition from &quot;stress&quot; to &quot;fracture&quot;—where distinct threat vectors (workforce exhaustion, economic toxicity, infrastructural obsolescence, digital fragility) converge into a unified poly-crisis threatening the continuity of care on a planetary scale.
                      </p>
                    </div>

                    <div className="grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-4">
                      {executiveMetrics.map((metric, idx) => (
                        <div key={idx} className="rounded-lg bg-white border border-slate-200 p-4">
                          <div className="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">{metric.value}</div>
                          <div className="text-xs text-slate-600 mt-1">{metric.label}</div>
                          <Badge variant={metric.badge as any} className="mt-2 text-xs">{metric.category}</Badge>
                        </div>
                      ))}
                    </div>

                    <div className="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
                      <h6 className="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">The Threat Matrix</h6>
                      <p className="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                        The audit identifies 50 critical negative news events serving as sentinel indicators. In the UK and Canada, universal access is nullified by wait times turning ERs into mortuaries. In the US, financialization has weaponized &quot;prior authorization&quot; into algorithmic denial. In emerging economies like India, physical safety of infrastructure is in question, with fire tragedies and spurious drug scandals eroding trust.
                      </p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </CardContent>
              </Card>

              {/* Chapter 1: Workforce Collapse */}
              <Card className="glass-card">
                <CardHeader>
                  <CardTitle className="text-lg flex items-center gap-2">
                    <Users className="h-5 w-5 text-purple-500" />
                    Chapter 1: The Workforce Collapse
                  </CardTitle>
                  <CardDescription>The Human Vector—Demographic and Professional Crisis</CardDescription>
                </CardHeader>
                <CardContent>
                  <div className="space-y-4">
                    <div className="rounded-lg bg-purple-50 border border-purple-200 p-4">
                      <h5 className="font-semibold text-purple-900 mb-2">The Mathematics of Scarcity</h5>
                      <p className="text-sm text-purple-700">
                        The AAMC projects a physician shortage of <strong>86,000 by 2036</strong> in the US alone. The shortage is most acute in primary care—the gatekeeping function. The U.S. Chamber of Commerce has declared a &quot;National Nursing Crisis&quot; with the aging population creating a pincer movement: demand for complex geriatric care rises as experienced caregivers retire.
                      </p>
                    </div>

                    <div className="grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-2">
                      <div className="rounded-lg bg-white border border-slate-200 p-4">
                        <h6 className="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">Burnout &amp; Moral Injury</h6>
                        <p className="text-xs text-slate-600 mb-2">
                          AMA President Dr. Jesse M. Ehrenfeld characterized the shortage as an &quot;urgent crisis&quot; driven by administrative burdens, attacks on science, and broken Medicare payment. Burnout directly correlates with increased medical errors, missed care, and poor patient outcomes.
                        </p>
                        <div className="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs">
                          <Badge variant="destructive">Critical</Badge>
                          <span className="text-slate-500">10% decrease due to AI, but remains &quot;stubbornly high&quot;</span>
                        </div>
                      </div>

                      <div className="rounded-lg bg-white border border-slate-200 p-4">
                        <h6 className="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">The Global Strike Wave</h6>
                        <p className="text-xs text-slate-600 mb-2">
                          38 distinct healthcare strikes in 2025. NHS resident doctors walked out for 5 days. University of California saw 40,000 workers strike. These strikes signal unsafe working conditions and broken labor relations.
                        </p>
                        <div className="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs">
                          <Badge variant="warning">Escalating</Badge>
                          <span className="text-slate-500">Workforce demands unsafe staffing ratios</span>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>

                    <div className="rounded-lg bg-rose-50 border border-rose-200 p-4">
                      <h6 className="font-semibold text-rose-900 mb-2">Violence Against Healers</h6>
                      <p className="text-sm text-rose-700">
                        In the UK, patient violence hit <strong>285 incidents per day</strong> by January 2026—nearly 300,000 assaults over three years. In India, doctors demand central protection laws following attacks. This creates a feedback loop: staff leave due to safety concerns, wait times increase, and patient aggression rises.
                      </p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </CardContent>
              </Card>

              {/* Chapter 2: Access Crisis */}
              <Card className="glass-card">
                <CardHeader>
                  <CardTitle className="text-lg flex items-center gap-2">
