                      <h5 className="font-semibold text-red-900 mb-2">The &quot;Hallway Medicine&quot; Death Toll</h5>
                      <p className="text-sm text-red-700">
                        The most critical category is death during waiting—logistical failures where treatment never began. UK: 85-year-old died after <strong>52-hour wait</strong> in A&amp;E corridor without Parkinson&apos;s medication. Canada: Patient died after <strong>33-hour wait</strong> for a bed. US: Patient died in bathroom after <strong>29-minute call for help</strong> was ignored.
                      </p>
                    </div>

                    <div className="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
