                      Abu Dhabi healthcare is navigating profound structural re-engineering, transitioning from reactive clinical models to proactive technology-enabled longevity ecosystems. The life sciences cluster is projected to contribute <strong>AED 94 billion to GDP by 2045</strong>, attracting AED 42 billion in investment.
