              {/* Three Structural Challenges */}
              <Card className="glass-card bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-50 to-purple-50 border-indigo-200">
                <CardHeader>
                  <CardTitle className="text-lg text-indigo-900">Three Primary Structural Challenges</CardTitle>
                </CardHeader>
                <CardContent>
                  <div className="space-y-4">
                    <div className="flex items-start gap-3">
                      <ShieldAlert className="h-5 w-5 text-rose-600 mt-0.5 shrink-0" />
                      <div>
                        <h4 className="font-semibold text-rose-900 text-sm">The Digital Trust Chasm</h4>
                        <p className="text-xs text-slate-700">As the system pivots to &quot;Healthcare in the Cloud&quot; and AI, vulnerability to cyberattacks becomes a critical reputational threat. Digital sovereignty must be communicated as resident protection.</p>
                      </div>
                    </div>

                    <div className="flex items-start gap-3">
                      <MessageSquare className="h-5 w-5 text-orange-600 mt-0.5 shrink-0" />
                      <div>
                        <h4 className="font-semibold text-orange-900 text-sm">Linguistic and Cultural Alignment</h4>
                        <p className="text-xs text-slate-700">The &quot;Consistency Gap&quot; in front-end service delivery requires massive investment in empathy training and multilingual clarity.</p>
                      </div>
                    </div>

                    <div className="flex items-start gap-3">
                      <Users className="h-5 w-5 text-purple-600 mt-0.5 shrink-0" />
                      <div>
                        <h4 className="font-semibold text-purple-900 text-sm">Influencer Authenticity vs. Regulation</h4>
                        <p className="text-xs text-slate-700">The Advertiser Permit system ensures safety but may create a credibility void if influencers lose authentic voice. ADPHC should foster diverse SIL matrix.</p>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </CardContent>
              </Card>

              {/* Strategic Conclusions */}
              <Card className="glass-card">
                <CardHeader>
                  <CardTitle className="text-lg text-cyan-900 flex items-center gap-2">
                    <Target className="h-5 w-5" />
                    Strategic Outlook
                  </CardTitle>
                </CardHeader>
                <CardContent>
                  <div className="space-y-3">
                    <p className="text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
                      The re-engineering of Abu Dhabi healthcare is a high-stakes endeavor balancing visionary growth with immediate operational friction. The <strong>AED 94 billion GDP contribution goal</strong> is powerful, but success depends on the &quot;Golden Threads&quot; of trust and resident experience.
                    </p>

                    <div className="grid gap-2 md:grid-cols-2 mt-4">
                      <div className="p-3 bg-gradient-to-br from-emerald-50 to-teal-50 rounded-lg border border-emerald-200">
                        <h4 className="font-semibold text-emerald-900 text-sm mb-1">From Managing to Thriving</h4>
                        <p className="text-xs text-slate-700">Ensuring residents are not just &quot;managed&quot; by a system, but thriving within a supportive ecosystem</p>
                      </div>

                      <div className="p-3 bg-gradient-to-br from-fuchsia-50 to-purple-50 rounded-lg border border-fuchsia-200">
                        <h4 className="font-semibold text-fuchsia-900 text-sm mb-1">Global Model for Longevity</h4>
                        <p className="text-xs text-slate-700">Positioning Abu Dhabi as the world&apos;s model for longevity and metabolic health innovation</p>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </CardContent>
              </Card>
            </div>
          </GlassPanel>
        </TabsContent>
      </Tabs>
    </div>
  )
}

